          • [ - ] Pico09 - member since 27-Aug-14

            I don't think this Barca team is as good as the results suggest. In this game, their passing and positional play wasn't very good. Alba and Rakitic, in particular, made too many mistakes and misplaced passes, which, fortunately for Barca, weren't punished by Atletico. And this wasn't an isolated case. Alba and Rakitic tend to often make some big mistakes which can easily lead to scoring opportunities for their opponents; Barca just hasn't been punished for those mistakes so far. Also, when things aren't going his way, Alba tends to panic. And then there's Barca's general struggle to create chances, which I think is somewhat due to Barca only playing with 1 forward and the fact that Messi is often playing with 2 lines of defenders infront of him, whereas in the past he would mostly face the back line, recieving the ball between the opponent's midfield and defense. If Barca play like this against Chelsea, then I think there's a good chance they might get knocked out of the UCL.
